tweet_text: 14 on july 31st 2023 the crossborder payments interoperability and extension taskforce was revealed by the bank for international settlements bis  as many of you know ripple was included  but who else were included and what can they offer  my thesis is that they included ripple since its a solution to provide global interoperability for lowvalue high frequency payments at first and in more illiquid currencies even though ripple is capable of wholesale operations my thesis is that its not the primary reason theyre added  do we have any other solutions focused on interoperability amongst illiquid currencies that are lowvalue high frequency  i went through them all and first looked at which ones offer global interoperability versus which ones are just for a certain region  i noted the global ones   cls  fnality  mastercard  ripple  rtgs global  swift  worldline  then i looked at which ones are only wholesale   cls   fnality  rtgs global  so then were left with   mastercard  ripple  swift swift go  worldline
tweet_raw: 1/4On July 31st 2023 the cross-border payments interoperability and extension taskforce was revealed by the Bank for international settlements (BIS).As many of you know Ripple was included.But who else were included and what can they offer?My thesis is that they included Ripple since its a solution to provide global interoperability for low-value high frequency payments (at first) and in more illiquid currencies (even though Ripple is capable of wholesale operations my thesis is that its not the primary reason theyre added).Do we have any other solutions focused on interoperability amongst illiquid currencies that are low-value high frequency?I went through them all and first looked at which ones offer global interoperability versus which ones are just for a certain region?I noted the Global ones:- CLS- Fnality- Mastercard- Ripple- RTGS global- Swift- WorldlineThen I looked at which ones are only wholesale:- CLS - Fnality- RTGS globalSo then were left with:- Mastercard- Ripple- Swift (Swift go?)- Worldline

tweet_raw: In the autumn of 2012 well before Craig Wright gained global recognition he discreetly submitted his initial patent tied to the nascent Bitcoin then valued at a mere ten dollars. The subsequent year witnessed the relatively obscure Coinbase exchange raising five million dollars with the explicit goal of simplifying Bitcoin usage for the average consumer. Fast forward to 2014 when Vitalik Buterin co-founder of Bitcoin Magazine penned an article introducing Ethereum an innovative blockchain. Buterin duly credited the pseudonymous Satoshi Nakamoto for groundbreaking strides in cryptography.While the budding cryptocurrency industry fixated on Bitcoins permissive code license – essentially allowing anyone to use the software within copyright bounds – Wright took a different route actively seeking patent protection for novel approaches to harness the technology. By December 2015 when two news organizations pegged him as a potential Satoshi Nakamoto Wright had notched two personal patent applications and held the position of Chief Scientist at nChain a Switzerland-based firm concurrently pursuing three additional patents.Whats your take on whether Craig is the creator of Bitcoin? #Bitcoin #CRAIGWRIGHT@Dr_CSWright @satoshi

tweet_text: tether savages united nations in response to moneylaundering report   just yesterday a report was published by the united nations office on drugs and crime claiming that tether_tos usdt was at the heart of various scams and moneylaundering   tether has now issued its own official response to the report both defending itself and issuing damning criticism of the un and its practices  tethers savage response  we are disappointed in the uns assessment that singles out usdt highlighting its involvement in illicit activity   the report goes on to accuse the un of  ignoring its role in helping developing economies in emerging markets completely neglected by the global financial world simply because servicing such communities would be unprofitable for them   tether points to its extensive cooperation with law enforcement authorities including the doj fbi and usss which was recently onboarded on the tether platform   it also makes the technological argument that the public blockchains upon which usdt is hosted are transparent and traceable in their very nature  the uns analysis ignores the traceability of tether tokens and the proven record tether has of collaborating with law enforcement   tether even accuses the un of having insufficient understanding and conducting insufficient research into blockchain technology and cryptocurrency  the absence of efforts to comprehend its fundamentals raises alarms about achieving the intended goals   the company highlights the more than 300 million that it has proven in recent months as part of its collaboration with authorities    tethers response ends by inviting collaboration with the un to help it better understanding crypto and its architecture  we also extend an invitation to the un to engage in collaborative dialogue echoing successful collaborations with dozens of global law enforcement agencies  image financial times cryptoregulation bitcoin ethereum stablecoin
tweet_raw: TETHER SAVAGES UNITED NATIONS IN RESPONSE TO MONEY-LAUNDERING REPORT- Just yesterday a report was published by the United Nations’ Office on Drugs and Crime claiming that @Tether_to’s $USDT was “at the heart” of various scams and money-laundering.- Tether has now issued its own official response to the report both defending itself and issuing damning criticism of the UN and its practices.Tether’s Savage Response…“We are disappointed in the UN’s assessment that singles out USDT highlighting its involvement in illicit activity”- The report goes on to accuse the UN of…“ignoring its role in helping developing economies in emerging markets completely neglected by the global financial world simply because servicing such communities would be unprofitable for them”- #Tether points to its extensive cooperation with law enforcement authorities including the “DOJ FBI and USSS (which was recently onboarded on the Tether platform)”.- It also makes the technological argument that the public blockchains upon which #USDT is hosted are transparent and traceable in their very nature.“The UN’s analysis ignores the traceability of Tether tokens and the proven record Tether has of collaborating with law enforcement”- Tether even accuses the UN of having insufficient understanding and conducting insufficient research into #blockchain technology and #cryptocurrency…“The absence of efforts to comprehend its fundamentals raises alarms about achieving the intended goals”- The company highlights the more than $300 million that it has proven in recent months as part of its collaboration with authorities. - Tether’s response ends by inviting collaboration with the UN to help it better understanding #crypto and its architecture.“We also extend an invitation to the UN to engage in collaborative dialogue echoing successful collaborations with dozens of global law enforcement agencies”Image: Financial Times#CryptoRegulation #Bitcoin #Ethereum #Stablecoin

tweet_raw: 🚨BREAKING: Elon considering using BitcoinSV and Doge as payment rails on X: Decision hinges on COPA v. Wright trial🚨Building the future of XX and @elonmusk  explore Unbounded #BitcoinSV and #Dogecoin for platform paymentsX under the guidance of Elon Musk X is currently investigating the potential integration of Unbounded BitcoinSV $BSV and Dogecoin $DOGE as payment options for transactions across the platform. We are committed to exploring these options and making informed decisions that benefit our users and the wider crypto community.X will continue to research and evaluate the potential integration of Unbounded BitcoinSV and Dogecoin with a focus on ensuring a smooth and secure user experience. The exchange cited Shibariums innovative technology as a key driving factor behind its decision. This endorsement from a market leader like OKX is a clear indicator of Shibariums growing influence and technological prowess.A Win for the Shiba Inu CommunityThis collective endorsement from major exchanges is a significant victory for the Shiba Inu community. tweet_raw: 🇮🇹 NOT TO MISS: in #Sorrento the presentation of the catalogue of the  the exhibition LA FIGURA E IL PAESAGGIO. Percorsi nella pittura napoletana del Novecento” on January 19th 2024 at 5.30 pm at #FIORENTINOVILLA in Corso Italia n. 53.The exhibition and the catalogue are made up with two parts and two volumes curated by the 🇮🇹 art historian #IsabellaValente with the cooperation of the 🇺🇸 art historian #PamelaPotter_Hennessey.The first part offers a general view introducing 32 Neapolitan masters of the 20th century (born between  the second part of the 19th century and the first decades of the 20thcentury ).The second part makes a specific focus on one of these 32 artists Domenico Fiorentino ( 1923-2012)  the painter of Sorrento titled “LA FIGURA ED IL PAESAGGIO Percorsi nella pittura di Domenico Fiorentino   e degli artisti americani vissuti a Sorrento”.It also includes 60 oil paintings on #Paris by #DomenicoFiorentino dated  1982-1989 presented for the first time to the public.The exhibition will remain open until January 28th 2024.

tweet_raw: From a Facebook post.It’s -45 this morning. I saw a fellow sitting in his EV at a charging station.
